<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1506,2034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,1615,1639]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<number box="[375,403,1614,1638]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="12.0">12</number>
medusae assigned to this species varied from 
<quantity box="[923,1074,1614,1638]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="6.25" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5 to 10 mm</quantity>
in bell diameter and completely match the several available descriptions of 
<taxonomicName box="[633,717,1652,1675]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Eirenidae" genus="Eutima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="mira">
<emphasis box="[633,717,1652,1675]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. mira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The presence of only four tentacles in addition with the configuration of the gonads (four on the sub-umbrellar portion of the radial canals, and four on the gastric peduncle) is diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName box="[318,405,1724,1747]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Eirenidae" genus="Eutima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="mira">
<emphasis box="[318,405,1724,1747]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. mira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the 
<number box="[540,568,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="23.0">23</number>
recognized species of the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="McCrady" box="[962,1138,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="McCrady, J. (1857) Gymnophthalmata of Charleston Harbor. Proceedings of the Elliott Society of Natural History of Charleston, 1, 103 - 221." type="journal article" year="1857">
McCrady 
<number box="[1079,1138,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1857.0">1857</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kramp" box="[1153,1299,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Kramp, P. L. (1961) Synopsis of the Medusae of the World. Journal of Marine Biological Associated of the United Kingdom, 40, 1 - 469." type="journal article" year="1961">
Kramp 
<number box="[1240,1299,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1961.0">1961</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Goy" box="[1314,1431,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Goy, J. (1979) Campagne de la Calypso au large des cotes atlantiques de l´Amerique du sud (1961 - 1962). Meduses. Resultats Scientifiques des Campagnes de la Calypso, 11, 263 - 296." type="journal article" year="1979">
Goy 
<number box="[1372,1431,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1979.0">1979</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouillon" box="[151,317,1758,1782]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Bouillon, J. (1999) Hydromedusae. In: Boltovskoy, D. (Ed) South Atlantic Zooplankton. Backhuys Publishers, Leiden, pp. 424 - 512." type="book chapter" year="1999">
Bouillon 
<number box="[258,317,1758,1782]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouillon" box="[330,563,1758,1783]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Bouillon, J., Gravili, C., Pages, F., Gili, J. - M. &amp; Boero, F. (2006) An introduction to the Hydrozoa. Memoirs du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris, 591 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Bouillon 
<emphasis box="[437,488,1758,1783]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[503,563,1758,1782]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Guo" box="[576,760,1758,1783]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Guo, D., Xu, Z. &amp; Huang, J. (2008) Two new species of Eirenidae from the coast of southeast China. Acta Oceanologica Sinica, 27 (1), 61 - 66." type="journal article" year="2008">
Guo 
<emphasis box="[633,684,1758,1783]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[700,760,1758,1782]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert" box="[772,963,1758,1782]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Schuchert, P. (2009 a) World Hydrozoa database. Available from http: // www. marinespecies. org / hydrozoa (accessed 29 November 2011)." type="journal article" year="2009" yearSuffix="a">
Schuchert 
<number box="[893,951,1758,1782]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2009.0">2009</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
) and easily differentiate it from the other two Brazilian species, 
<taxonomicName authority="L. Agassiz" authorityName="L. Agassiz" box="[405,681,1794,1819]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Eirenidae" genus="Eutima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="coerulae">
<emphasis box="[405,534,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. coerulae</emphasis>
(L. Agassiz)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Narchi &amp; Hebling, 1975" authorityName="Narchi &amp; Hebling" authorityYear="1975" box="[736,1154,1794,1819]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Eirenidae" genus="Eutima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="sapinhoa">
<emphasis box="[736,870,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. sapinhoa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Narchi" box="[877,1154,1794,1818]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Narchi, W. &amp; Hebling, N. J. (1975) The life cycle of the commensal hydromedusa Eutima sapinhoa n. sp. Marine Biology, 30, 73 - 78." type="journal article" year="1975">
Narchi &amp; Hebling, 
<number box="[1095,1154,1794,1818]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1975.0">1975</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which possess only four gonads (
<bibRefCitation author="Narchi" box="[245,514,1830,1854]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Narchi, W. &amp; Hebling, N. J. (1975) The life cycle of the commensal hydromedusa Eutima sapinhoa n. sp. Marine Biology, 30, 73 - 78." type="journal article" year="1975">
Narchi &amp; Hebling 
<number box="[455,514,1830,1854]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1975.0">1975</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, Migotto 
<emphasis box="[623,672,1830,1855]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 2002, 2004). Reports on 
<taxonomicName box="[964,1048,1831,1855]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Eirenidae" genus="Eutima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="mira">
<emphasis box="[964,1048,1831,1855]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. mira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicate that their tentacular bulbs may or may not have lateral cirri. All medusae analyzed herein had cirri on rudimentary bulbs only.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1506,2034]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,354,1902,1927]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[361,445,1903,1927]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Eirenidae" genus="Eutima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="mira">
<emphasis box="[361,445,1903,1927]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. mira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be found in 
<collectingCountry box="[632,699,1902,1926]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">China</collectingCountry>
Seas and is widely distributed along the western Atlantic coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[151,207,1938,1962]" name="United States of America" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kramp" box="[222,370,1938,1962]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Kramp, P. L. (1961) Synopsis of the Medusae of the World. Journal of Marine Biological Associated of the United Kingdom, 40, 1 - 469." type="journal article" year="1961">
Kramp 
<number box="[310,370,1938,1962]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1961.0">1961</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In the southwestern Atlantic there are two records off northeastern Brazil—around Fernando de Noronha Island (~ 
<geoCoordinate box="[397,485,1974,1998]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" precision="925" value="-3.85">
<number box="[397,411,1974,1998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0">3</number>
° 
<number box="[422,453,1974,1998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="51.0">51</number>
’ S
</geoCoordinate>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vannucci" box="[499,672,1974,1998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Vannucci, M. (1957) On Brazilian hydromedusae and their distribution in relation to different water masses. Boletim do Instituto Oceanografico da Universidade de Sao Paulo, 8 (1 - 2), 23 - 109." type="journal article" year="1957">Vannucci 1957</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vannucci" box="[685,745,1974,1998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Vannucci, M. (1958) Consideracoes em torno das hidromedusas da regiao de Fernando de Noronha. Boletim do Instituto Oceanografico da Universidade de Sao Paulo, 9, 3 - 12." type="journal article" year="1958">1958</bibRefCitation>
), and off Alagoas (~ 
<number box="[983,998,1974,1998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.0">9</number>
°S) and Bahia coastal waters (
<geoCoordinate box="[1343,1436,1974,1998]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" precision="925" value="-12.933333">
<number box="[1343,1373,1974,1998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="12.0">12</number>
° 
<number box="[1383,1415,1974,1998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="56.0">56</number>
’S
</geoCoordinate>
and 
<geoCoordinate box="[198,293,2010,2034]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" precision="925" value="-16.483334">
<number box="[198,229,2010,2034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="16.0">16</number>
° 
<number box="[239,272,2010,2034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="29.0">29</number>
’S
</geoCoordinate>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Goy" box="[305,418,2010,2034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Goy, J. (1979) Campagne de la Calypso au large des cotes atlantiques de l´Amerique du sud (1961 - 1962). Meduses. Resultats Scientifiques des Campagnes de la Calypso, 11, 263 - 296." type="journal article" year="1979">
Goy 
<number box="[361,418,2010,2034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1979.0">1979</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) – as well as two additional records from the temperate Argentinean shelf (
<number box="[1262,1339,2010,2034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="37.5" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="37.0">37–38</number>
°S; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zamponi" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Zamponi, M. O. (1983 a) Ecologia de las hidromedusas del Mar Epicontinental Argentino. Neotropica, 29 (81), 65 - 81." type="journal article" year="1983" yearSuffix="a">
Zamponi 
<number box="[208,267,151,175]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1983.0">1983</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zamponi" box="[292,582,151,175]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Zamponi, M. O. &amp; Suarez, E. (1991) Blooms of medusae on the shores of Mar del Plata (Argentina). Plankton Newsletter, 15, 19 - 20." type="journal article" year="1991">
Zamponi &amp; Suárez, 
<number box="[522,582,151,175]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The present finding is the first record of this hydromedusa from the south Brazilian coast and fulfills a gap of its known distribution.
</paragraph>
